Fitch Rates BofA Finance LLC's Sr. Debt Securities Program 'A' | Business Wire


























































      Fitch Rates BofA Finance LLC's Sr. Debt Securities Program 'A'
    





October 28, 2016 12:43 PM Eastern Daylight Time



CHICAGO--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Fitch Ratings has assigned a rating of 'A' to BofA Finance LLC's senior 
      debt securities program. Bank of America Corporation (BAC) has provided 
      an unconditional and irrevocable guarantee for payment of all amounts 
      due in respect of the securities.
    

      KEY RATING DRIVERS
    

      IDRS, VR AND SENIOR DEBT
    

      The senior debt securities of BofA Finance, LLC issued under the senior 
      debt securities program will be unconditionally guaranteed by BAC and 
      therefore the debt level rating of 'A' would change in conjunction with 
      any changes to BAC's Issuer Default Ratings (IDRs). Fitch affirmed BAC's 
      IDRs on June 14, 2016 with a Stable Outlook as part of its Global 
      Trading and Universal Bank (GTUB) periodic review. BAC's IDRs are 
      underpinned by a slowly improving earnings profile, the maintenance of 
      good liquidity levels, satisfactory capital ratios, and materially lower 
      litigation costs than at any point over the last few years. Please see 
      'Fitch Affirms Bank of America's Long-Term IDR at 'A'' (June 14, 2016) 
      for additional details.
    

      The rating on the debt securities program is based entirely on the 
      ratings of BAC, and it is Fitch's view that the notes rank pari passu 
      with senior, unsecured obligations of BAC. The guarantee will only cover 
      amounts that are due to the noteholder, which may be less than the par 
      value of the issuance.
    

      Additionally, there is no assurance that notes issued under the program 
      will be assigned a rating, or that the rating assigned to a specific 
      issue under the program will have the same rating as the program.
    

      RATING SENSITIVITIES
    

      The rating of this issuance is sensitive to any changes in BAC's IDR. 
      Ratings will move up or down in tandem with BAC's senior unsecured debt 
      ratings.
    

      Fitch has assigned the following rating:
    

      BofA Finance, LLC
    

      --Senior debt at 'A'.
    

      Additional information is available on www.fitchratings.com


      Applicable Criteria
    

      Global Bank Rating Criteria (pub. 15 Jul 2016)
    

https://www.fitchratings.com/site/re/884135


